cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on handling users' requests by scheduling computational jobs and assigning resources in data centers, which is a core issue in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also applies machine learning approaches, specifically LSTM neural network, to predict and classify the computing jobs, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised hierarchical clustering algorithm, BIRCH, to classify the computing jobs, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
